The 25th [[Cuban National Series]] was the first to feature four-team-playoffs with the first- and second-place teams from each of the new Western and Eastern zones.
Four teams qualified for the playoffs: [[Industriales]], [[Vegueros]], [[Santiago de Cuba (baseball team)|Santiago de Cuba]] and [[Villa Clara (baseball team)|Villa Clara]]. Industriales went undefeated in the [[Round-robin tournament|round-robin]] tournament, earning their sixth National Series title.
