{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox cricket ground |ground_name = ACA International Cricket Stadium |nickname = |caption = The Andhra Cricket Association international cricket stadium under construction at Mangalagiri |country = India |image = File:ACA international cricket stadium, Mangalagiri.jpg |coordinates = {{coord|16.437|80.553|display=inline, title}} |location = [[Mangalagiri]], [[Guntur district]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]] |establishment = TBA |seating_capacity = 40,000 |Flood Lights = Yes |owner = Sports Authority of Andhra Pradesh |operator = [[Andhra Cricket Association]] |tenants = [[Andhra cricket team]] |end1 = n/a |end2 = |international = true |firstodidate = |firstodiyear = |firstodihome = |firstodiaway = |lastodidate = |lastodiyear = |lastodihome = |lastodiaway = |firsttestdate = |firsttestyear = |firsttesthome = |firsttestaway = |lasttestdate = |lasttestyear = |lasttesthome = |lasttestaway = |date = |year = |source = }}
'''ACA International Cricket Stadium''' (or '''Andhra Cricket Association International Cricket Stadium''') is a cricket stadium under construction in the town of [[Mangalagiri]]. It is situated in [[Guntur district]] of the [[Indian state]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]], nearly {{convert|15|mi|abbr=on}} from [[Guntur]] and {{convert|10|mi|abbr=on}} from [[Vijayawada]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/ecofriendly-stadium-coming-up-at-mangalagiri/article4561744.ece|title=Eco-friendly stadium coming up at Mangalagiri|date=2013-03-29|newspaper=The Hindu|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|access-date=2016-06-16}}</ref> [[Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy]] laid the foundation, with construction company IVRCL Limited winning the rights for the project, worth {{INRConvert|51.04|c|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/ivrcl-bags-orders-worth-rs-1098-crore/article4908462.ece|title=IVRCL bags orders worth Rs 1,098 crore|last=Bureau|first=Our|date=2013-07-12|website=The Hindu Business Line|access-date=2016-06-16}}</ref> It is owned by [[Andhra Cricket Association]].and spread over an area of {{Convert|24|acres|abbr=on}} with a seating capacity of 40,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/andhra_pradesh/International-cricket-stadium-for-Vijaywada-near-NTR-health-university/2016/05/29/article3455734.ece|title=International cricket stadium for Vijaywada near NTR health university|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2016-06-16}}</ref><ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/ACA%E2%80%99s-Mangalagiri-stadium-to-be-ready-by-2018/article14995301.ece ACA’s Mangalagiri stadium to be ready by 2018]</ref>
[[VVS Laxman]], the former [[Indian cricket team|Indian batsman]] has inaugurated the Central Zone Academy of [[Andhra Cricket Association]] in June 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/vvs-laxman-inaugurates-andhra-cricket-associations-central-zone-academy/1130555/|title=ACA Central Zone Academy|publisher=indianexpress| accessdate=2014-05-11}}</ref> The stadium will include a club house and an indoor cricket academy. The [[Board of Control for Cricket in India]] made [[Andhra Cricket Association]] as the headquarters of [[Indian women's cricket team]].<ref name=":0" />
