{{Primary sources|date=December 2009}}
The '''Canadian Academy of Sport and Exercise Medicine''' (CASEM) is the national [[medicine|medical]] specialty society for [[sport medicine]] [[physician]]s in [[Canada]]. The Academy is open for membership to [[medical doctor]]s (MD) within Canada and internationally.  Founded in 1970, the Academy serves as a means to ensure its members are kept up to date with current medical practices in sport medicine.  The '''Diploma in Sport Medicine'''<!-- redirects here --> (Dip. Sport Med.) developed by CASEM, is the recognized credential in Canada for sport medicine physicians. The '''''Clinical Journal of Sport Medicine'''''<!-- redirects here -->, founded by CASEM, is a peer reviewed sport medicine journal, now published by [[Lippincott Williams & Wilkins]].

