'''Crokicurl''' is a Canadian [[winter sport]] invented by Public City Architecture and first played in [[Winnipeg]], Canada.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/crokicurl-game-rink-opens-in-calgary-1.4481238|title=Crokicurl ready for its Calgary closeup {{!}} CBC News|work=CBC|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/saskatoon/australian-tries-crokicurl-saskatoon-1.4496487|title=Reporter from Down Under learns to play ultra-Canadian crokicurl game|work=CBC News|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Super Canadian' ice game crokicurl kicks off at The Forks {{!}} CBC News |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/crokicurl-winnipeg-kick-off-1.3956876 |accessdate=23 August 2018 |work=CBC News |agency=CBC News |publisher=CBC News |date=January 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Turner |first1=Randy |title=No joke-i-king! Crokicurling is a thing |url=https://www.winnipegfreepress.com/local/no-joke-i-king-crokicurling-is-a-thing-411931905.html |website=Winnipeg Free Press |publisher=Winnipeg Free Press |accessdate=23 August 2018 |date=26 January 2017}}</ref>
The game is a large scale hybrid of [[curling]] and the board game [[Crokinole]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.manitoulin.ca/2018/02/28/crokicurl-curling-meets-crokinole/|title='Crokicurl:' curling meets crokinole|last=McCutcheon|first=Alicia|date=2018-02-28|work=Manitoulin Expositor|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ckom.com/2018/02/17/final-days-to-try-crokicurl-in-saskatoon/|title=Final days to try crokicurl in Saskatoon|last=News|first=CKOM|work=650 CKOM|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cjme.com/2018/02/13/244317/|title=Crokicurl makes its way to Regina|last=Gray|first=Britton|work=980 CJME|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/3951464/crokicurl-begins-second-season-at-the-forks/|title=Crokicurl begins second season at The Forks|work=CJOB|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en}}</ref> Crokinole is a game in which the players take turn to flick small discs on a circular board, to score highest depending on where the disc lands on the board where the regions are marked with score.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.energeticcity.ca/2018/02/city-council-looking-bringing-crokicurl-energetic-city/|title=City Council looking at bringing crokicurl to the Energetic City - Energeticcity.ca|date=2018-02-19|work=Energeticcity.ca|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en-US}}</ref> In the crokicurl version of the game, rocks are used instead of discs which are roughly the size of a curling stone. The stones are made from a lighter material. The game is played by teams consisting of two players, trying to score points by throwing the stones into the center of the ice where the circles are marked. The highest circle is marked with twenty points.<ref name=":0" />
Crokicurl is played in [[Winnipeg]], [[Saskatoon]], [[Regina, Saskatchewan|Regina]] and [[Fort St. John, British Columbia|Fort St. John]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thestarphoenix.com/news/local-news/crokicurl-makes-its-saskatoon-debut-on-broadway-avenue|title=Crokicurl makes its Saskatoon debut on Broadway Avenue|date=2018-01-19|work=Saskatoon StarPhoenix|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cjme.com/2018/01/19/crokicurl-sliding-into-the-queen-city-soon/|title=Crokicurl sliding into the Queen City soon|last=News|first=CJME|work=980 CJME|access-date=2018-03-15|language=en}}</ref>
