{{Spoken Wikipedia|Paralympics New Zealand.ogg|2012-6-6}} {{Infobox National Paralympic Committee | title = Paralympics New Zealand | logo = Paralympics New Zealand logo.svg | size = 200px | country = New Zealand | code = NZL | created = 1968 | recognized = | association = OPC | headquarters = [[Parnell, New Zealand|Parnell]], [[Auckland]] | president = | secretary general = | website = [http://www.paralympics.org.nz/ paralympics.org.nz] }} '''Paralympics New Zealand''' (PNZ) is the [[National Paralympic Committee]] in [[New Zealand]] for the [[Paralympic Games]] movement. It oversees the means by which New Zealand participates at the [[Summer Paralympics]] and the [[Winter Paralympics]].
PNZ is affiliated to the [https://www.paralympic.org International Paralympic Committee] as the [http://www.paralympics.org.nz National Paralympic Committee] for New Zealand. It is one of [https://www.paralympic.org/the-ipc/national-paralympic-committees 170 NPC’s worldwide], responsible for supporting and growing [[Paralympic_sports|Paralympic Sports]] in their countries.
PNZ is a charity overseeing up to [http://www.paralympics.org.nz/Para-Sport/About-Para-Sport/Types-of-Para-Sport 22 Paralympic Sports] disciplines and delivery of the [http://hpsnz.org.nz High Performance Sports Programme] within a number of disciplines. PNZ prepares, selects and leads New Zealand teams to international competitions and the Paralympic Games.
PNZ works with athletes, members, partners and government agencies to inspire those living with a disability in New Zealand society and increase awareness, understanding and acceptance of disability amongst the wider public.
==See also== *[[New Zealand at the Paralympics]] *[[New Zealand Olympic Committee]]
