{{For|the men's team|Soviet Union national rugby union team}}
The '''[[Soviet Union]] women's national [[rugby union]] team''' played six matches between 1990 and 1991. The team was severely underfunded, surviving the 1991 World Cup by bartering and selling items of kit and other trinkets. They ceased playing after 1991, because of the [[History of the Soviet Union (1985–1991)#Dissolution of the USSR|collapse of the Soviet Union]].
