{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Yusuf Ziya Öniş Stadium | nickname = | image = | location = [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]] {{flagicon|Turkey}}| broke_ground = | opened = 2009| renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Ministry of Youth and Sports | operator = | surface = Turf | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[Sarıyer G.K.]]| seating_capacity = 10.000 | }}
'''Yusuf Ziya Öniş Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Istanbul]], [[Turkey]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the [[Home team|home ground]] of [[TFF Second League]] team [[Sarıyer G.K.]]. <ref>[http://www.sariyersporkulubu.org.tr/2013/yusuf-ziya-onis-stadyumu/ Sariyer]; ''Sariyer Spor Kulube''. Retrieved on 1 July 2013</ref> The stadium was built in 2009 and currently holds 10,000 people.
