{{Infobox venue | name = İlkadım Athletics Stadium | nickname = | native_name = İlkadım Atletizm Stadı | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = Turkey | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location of the stadium in Turkey. | pushpin_label_position = | address = Liman Mah., Ataturk Boulevard 93, İlkadım | location = [[İlkadım]], [[Samsun Province|Samsun]], Turkey | coordinates = 4{{coord|41|18|31|N|36|20|08|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{start date and age|2017}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = around {{Turkish lira}} 20 million (approx. US$ 8.5 million) | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 2,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''İlkadım Athletics Stadium'''({{lang-tr|İlkadım Atletizm Stadı}}) is a [[track and field]] facility located in [[İlkadım]] district of [[Samsun Province]], northern Turkey. It was built for the 2017 Summer Deaflympics.
The stadium is situated at Liman Mah., Ataturk Boulevard 93 in İlkadım. The athletics stadium was built in place of a former 1,500-seat football stadium, which was built in 1958. The old stadium was renovated and brought to [[International Association of Athletics Federations|IAAF]] standards by adding a synthetic-surface track in 2001. The area for athletics events totaled to {{convert|6500|m2|sqft|abbr=on}}. With the modernization and expansion of [[Samsun 19 Mayıs Stadium]], the old stadium was converted into an athletics-only stadium in April 2010 that caused public reation.<ref name="d1"/> By November 2014, the old stadium, which did not meet the requirements any more,<ref name="gsb"/> was demolished to make place for a modern athletics stadium.<ref name="skh"/> The projected cost of the construction was around {{Turkish lira}} 20 million (approx. US$ 8.5 million). The stadium was built for the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]].<ref name="gsb"/> The venue has a seating capacity for 2,000 spectators, including 100 for [[Very important person|VIP]], 200 for media members, 200 for accredited sportspeople and 100 for physically handicapped people.<ref name="d"/>
==International events hosted== The venue will host athletics events of the 2017 Summer Deaflympics.<ref name="d"/>
